You can embed dashboards using Experience Builder or Visualforce pages.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

USER PERMISONS NEEDED
To use CRM Analytics, users need:
- Setup permissions to enable sharing with Communities
- Access to the Sharing dialog
- Security predicates setup

Security is enforced at these levels:
- By role, group, or user, via the Sharing dialog
- At the CRM Analytics app level, via the Enable sharing with Communities checkbox
- At the org setup level, via security predicates

To embed dashboards in Experience Cloud sites, you can use:
- Experience Builder
- Visualforce
- LWC CRM Analytics Dashboard component

Annotations allow partners and customers to converse in Chatter feeds on individual dashboard widgets.

You can open Salesforce records and perform record-level actions and bulk actions from CRM Analytics in Experience Cloud sites.

Before setting up an Experience Cloud site with CRM Analytics, keep these best practices in mind:
- Use security predicates to control security
- Use the LWC CRM Analytics Dashboard component for a seamless experience
title: Sharing Salesforce Analytics in Experience Cloud Sites
